title: ICE: `fn_arg_names: unexpected item`

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: requires-nightly
labels.description: This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way.

labels.name: S-has-mcve
labels.description: A Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example has been found for this issue

body:
### Code ```Rust // run-pass #![feature(intrinsics)] mod dst { extern "rust-intrinsic" { pub fn dst(dst: *mut dst, dst: dst, dst: dst) -> dst; } } pub fn dst() { unsafe { let mut dst: dst<_> = dst::dst(1); } } pub fn main() {} ``` This crashes with `rustc 1.68.0-nightly (107233789 2022-12-19)` while `rustc 1.68.0-nightly (d0dc9efff 2022-12-18)` just gives an error. ### Error output ``` error[E0573]: expected type, found module `dst` --> 659b4bf9cb28826af248db582fdd0c70e77d41f3.rs:12:22 | 12 | let mut dst: dst<_> = dst::dst(1); | ^^^^^^ not a type warning: type parameter `dst` should have an upper camel case name --> 659b4bf9cb28826af248db582fdd0c70e77d41f3.rs:6:20 | 6 | pub fn dst(dst: *mut dst, dst: dst, dst: dst) -> dst; | ^^^ help: convert the identifier to upper camel case: `Dst` | = note: `#[warn(non_camel_case_types)]` on by default error[E0093]: unrecognized intrinsic function: `dst` --> 659b4bf9cb28826af248db582fdd0c70e77d41f3.rs:6:9 | 6 | pub fn dst(dst: *mut dst, dst: dst, dst: dst) -> dst; | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ unrecognized intrinsic error: internal compiler error: compiler/rustc_middle/src/hir/mod.rs:167:13: fn_arg_names: unexpected item DefId(0:5 ~ 659b4bf9cb28826af248db582fdd0c70e77d41f3[89ee]::dst::{extern#0}::dst) --> 659b4bf9cb28826af248db582fdd0c70e77d41f3.rs:6:9 | 6 | pub fn dst(dst: *mut dst, dst: dst, dst: dst) -> dst; | ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^ ```
